{% extends "_base.html.jinja" %}

{% block content %}
  {% with summary = {"title": "Aging WIP", "headline": aging.headline} %}
    {% include "_partials/metric_summary.html.jinja" %}
  {% endwith %}

  {% with mode = 'detail', data = aging %}
    {% include "_partials/aging_tile.html.jinja" %}
  {% endwith %}

  {% with data = work_items %}
    {% include "_partials/work_items_table.html.jinja" %}
  {% endwith %}

  <section class="detail-extras">
    <h2>How to read this</h2>
    <p>
      Each point is one <em>in-flight</em> work item (started but
      not yet completed at the as-of date), positioned at its
      current workflow state on the x-axis and elapsed age in days
      on the y-axis. The dashed reference lines are commitment
      thresholds from completed-item cycle times: P50, P85
      (Vacanti's external commitment), and P95 (high-stakes).
      An item aged past P85 is statistically likely to miss the
      forecast.
    </p>

    <h2>Caveats</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>The as-of date defaults to today (UTC). Pass
        <code>?asof=YYYY-MM-DD</code> for a historical view.</li>
      <li>Reference lines come from the same percentile distribution
        the cycle-time chart shows — they don't update with the
        as-of date, only with the underlying completed-item data.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Methodology</h2>
    <p>
      Per Vacanti, <em>Actionable Agile Metrics for Predictability</em>,
      10th Anniversary Edition: in-flight items are those created
      on or before the as-of date with no completion (or a
      completion strictly after the as-of date). Age = (asof −
      created_at.date()) in calendar days. Current state is the
      latest stage entered at or before the as-of date.
    </p>

    <h2>Actions</h2>
    <p><em>Reserved for future "now what?" suggestions — pull the
       oldest item into the standup, flag stalled work, etc.
       Empty in v1.</em></p>
  </section>

  <a class="back-link" href="/contracts/{{ contract.name }}/">← Back to dashboard</a>
{% endblock %}
